ian government]], and the colonies later merged with [[Cape Colony]] and [[Colony of Natal|Natal]] to form the [[Union of South Africa]] in 1910. Kruger had lived in exile from 7 May 1900 onward.\n| rowspan=\"3\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sahistory.org.za/article/aftermath-war|title=The Aftermath of the war|last=sahoboss|date=2011-03-31|website=South African History Online|language=en|access-date=2019-05-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/biography/Paul-Kruger|title=Paul Kruger {{!}} South African statesman|website=Encyclopedia Britannica|language=en|access-date=2019-05-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Schalk Willem Burger]]\n|[[State President of the South African Republic|Acting State President of the South African Republic]]\n|-\n|[[Christiaan de Wet]]\n|{{Flag|Orange Free State}}\n|[[State President of the Orange Free State]]\n|-\n|[[Gojong of Korea]]\n|rowspan=2|{{Flag|Korea|1899}}\n|rowspan=2|[[Emperor of Korea]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Flag|Empire of Japan|name=Japan}}\n|19 July 1907\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Korea under Japanese rule|Occupation of Korea]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=IgxvBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA144&dq=1907+Gojong+Korea#v=onepage&q=1907%20Gojong%20Korea&f=false|title=The History of Korea|last=Kim|first=Djun Kil|publisher=ABC-CLIO|year=2014|isbn=9781610695824|edition= 2nd|location=Santa Barbara. CA. Denver, CO and Oxford, UK|pages=144|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=wmdskbM_VgAC&pg=PT40&dq=1910+Sunjong#v=onepage&q=1910%20Sunjong&f=false|title=Primitive Selves: Koreana in the Japanese Colonial Gaze, 1910\u20131945|last=Atkins|first=E. Taylor|publisher=University of California Press|year=2010|isbn=9780520947689|location=Berkeley, CA, Los Angeles, CA and London, UK|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|chapter-url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=NMvOCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT34&dq=1910+Sunjong&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjAk6PzlOLhAhXEo4sKHfmMAZ8Q6AEINTAC#v=onepage&q