UC&pg=PT634&dq=Alexander+Dub%C4%8Dek+encyclopedia&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwic-5ymioDiAhVpoYsKHS0cCYgQ6AEIJzAA#v=onepage&q=Alexander%20Dub%C4%8Dek%20encyclopedia&f=false|title=Encyclopedia of the Cold War|last=Kramer|first=Mark|publisher=Routledge|year=2008|isbn=9781135923105|editor-last=Dijk|editor-first=Ruud van|location=New York and London|pages=|language=en|chapter=Dub\u010dek, Alexander|editor-last2=Gray|editor-first2=William Glenn|editor-last3=Savranskaya|editor-first3=Svetlana|editor-last4=Suri|editor-first4=Jeremi|editor-last5=Zhai|editor-first5=Qiang}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=gZzEYyB8X8YC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Alexander+Dub%C4%8Dek+1968#v=onepage&q=Alexander%20Dub%C4%8Dek%201968&f=false|title=The Prague Spring and the Warsaw Pact Invasion of Czechoslovakia in 1968|last=Kramer|first=Mark|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|year=2010|isbn=9780739143049|editor-last=Bischof|editor-first=G\u00fcnter|location=Lanham, Boulder, New York, Toronto and Plymouth, UK|pages=35|language=en|editor-last2=Karner|editor-first2=Stefan|editor-last3=Ruggenthaler|editor-first3=Peter}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Flag|Polish People's Republic|name=Poland}}\n|-\n|{{Flag|Hungarian People's Republic|name=Hungary}}\n|-\n|{{Flag|People's Republic of Bulgaria|1967|name=Bulgaria}}\n|-\n|{{Flag|East Germany}}\n|-\n|[[Philip Effiong]]\n|{{Flag|Biafra}}\n|[[President of Biafra]]\n|{{Flag|Nigeria}}\n|12 January 1970 \n|[[Nigerian Civil War]]\n|Effiong was only head of state for four days before surrendering to Nigeria. Biafra never received diplomatic recognition from the international community. \n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://biafra.info/biafra/nigeria-biafra-civil-war-effiong-surrenders-biafra.html|title=Archived copy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040804030106/http://biafra.info/biafra/nigeria-biafra-civil-war-effiong-surrenders-biafra.html|archive-date=4 August 2004|url-status=|access-date=10 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/place/Biafra|t